Interface SocketVirtualClient

All Superinterfaces:
VirtualClient
public interface SocketVirtualClient extends VirtualClient
Represents a virtual client specifically for Socket-based connections. This interface is primarily for structural and aesthetic purposes, allowing Socket clients to be treated similarly to other virtual client types without requiring additional methods specific to sockets within this interface itself.
